e64c3929-d8fa-49de-bd09-802c32a5f72b.0c3f85ef-aa98-4515-8f91-d4b22a790bb4.description=Purpose\:
 This step checks the paired values of the Data Pump parameters and updates when necessary values are missing specially when it relates to performance boost. It also checks the validity of its parameter contents. 


Inputs\:
 command - executes UpdateParametersforOracleDatabaseRefreshviaDataPumpv3.py
 Content - No description
 Data Options - *Optional\: The DATA_OPTIONS parameter provides options for how to handle certain types of data during exports and imports. The only valid option for this parameter is SKIP_CONSTRAINT_ERRORS.
 Data Pump Export Files - No description
 Data Pump Parameter File - No description
 Defaulted Parameters - No description
 Encryption Password - No description
 Exclude - *Optional\: Enables you to filter the metadata that is imported by specifying objects and object types that you want to exclude from the import job.
 Include - *Optional\: Enables you to filter the metadata that is imported by specifying objects and object types for the current import mode.
 Instance Wrapper - No description
 Job Name - *Optional\: Name of the import job to create.
 Oracle DB User - No description
 Oracle DB User Password - No description
 Oracle Home - No description
 Oracle SID - No description
 Oracle Version - No description
 Parallel - *Optional\: Change the number of active workers for current import job.
 Partition Options - *Optional\: Specifies how table partitions should be created during an import operation.
 Remap Data - *Optional\: This parameter allows you to remap data as it is being inserted into a new database.
 Remap Datafile - *Optional\: Comma separated key value pair of Tablespace Name\:Location of tablespace datafiles. Example\: USERS\:/u01/app/oracle/oradata/orca,SCOTT\:/u01/app/oracle/oradata/orca .
 Remap Tablespace - *Optional\: Remaps all objects selected for import with persistent data in the source tablespace to be created in the target tablespace.
 Schema - *Optional\: Specifies that a schema-mode import is to be performed
 Table Exist Action - No description
 Tables - *Optional\: Specifies that you want to perform a table-mode import.
 Tablespaces - *Optional\: Specifies that you want to perform a tablespace-mode import.
 Target Location - No description
 Update System Tables - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Data Pump Parameter File - No description
 Import Log File - No description
 Time Stamp - No description
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 e64c3929-d8fa-49de-bd09-802c32a5f72b.14299bc8-80c6-4d77-9eec-f1156f6d9790.description=Description\:

This step parses the Oracle inventory files that exists, or else it forwards the inventory information.

(1) If the inventory pointer files are specified and exist, parse these files extracting the contents.
(2) If and inventory file is specified and does not exist, ensure a valid specification.
(3) If no inventory file is specified, assign the appropriate default.

Dependencies\: Must run as the server superuser.

Return Code\: 

0 \= All files were found on the system.
1 \= Errors occured while checking files.

Inputs\:
 command - executes ParseOracleInventory.py
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 Oracle Account - Optional\: Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home. This is required only if inventory does not exist.
 Oracle Home - Optional\: The ORACLE_HOME to use if more than one Home is in the inventory file(s).
 Server Wrapper - Required\: String to execute routine as server superuser.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Cluster Nodes - Comma-separated list of all nodes where the Oracle Home is deployed.
 CRS Account - The OS owner of the ORA_CRS_HOME.
 CRS Active Version - The active CRS version.
 CRS Group - The Oracle group used for the ORA_CRS_HOME installation.
 CRS Home - The last ORA_CRS_HOME location in the inventory file.
 CRS Home Name - The name of the ORA_CRS_HOME as recorded in the inventory.
 CRS Nodes - Comma-separated list of all nodes where the Oracle Clusterware is deployed.
 Inventory Groups - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory groups. One for each Inventory Pointer.
 Inventory Locations - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory pathname directories.
 Inventory Pointers - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory pointer files.
 Oracle Account - Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home.
 Oracle Group - The Oracle group used for the ORACLE_HOME installation
 Oracle Home - The last ORACLE_HOME located in the inventory file or the user-inputted Oracle Home.
 Oracle Home Info - Dictionary list of all information discovered in the supplied inventory file(s).
 Oracle Home Name - The name of the ORACLE_HOME as recorded in the inventory.
 Oracle Listener Account - The OS owner of the ORACLE_HOME of the relevant listener.
 Oracle Version - Version of the Oracle Home.
 SQLPlus Version - Version of SQLPlus from Oracle Home.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

This step prepares the call wrappers needed to become the owner of the Oracle Database software and root. It sets the default values for call wrapper and Oracle OS owner variables used in subsequent workflow steps.

Dependencies\: None

Return code\:

0 \= All parameters are valid
1 \= At least one parameter is not valid

Inputs\:
 command - executes PrepareOracleCallWrapper.py
 Oracle Account - Required\: The user who owns ORACLE_HOME.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Boolean False - Boolean value for False
 Boolean True - Boolean value for True
 Instance Wrapper - Jython call wrapper to run as the Oracle Instance owner.
 No Value - Used to hide unused parameters in later steps.
 None Value - Value containing None
 Oracle Account - The user who owns ORACLE_HOME.
 Server Wrapper - Jython call wrapper to run as the admin user.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 e64c3929-d8fa-49de-bd09-802c32a5f72b.4f97fce5-a460-4666-b7f1-6147b8554597.description=Description\: 

Verifies access to the parameter file and executes the Data Pump Import utility.

Dependencies\: None

Return Code\:

0 \= Successful execution of the Data Pump Import utility.
1 \= Errors occurred while executing Data Pump Import utility.

Inputs\:
 command - executes ExecuteOracleRefreshviaDataPumpv3.py
 Cleanup Database - Optional\: If value is set to True cleanup will occur on the database and attempt to drop all non-default schemas. Default value is False.
 Cleanup Users Exclude - Optional\: Comma separated list of database users that should be excluded from the cleanup process.
 Ignorable Oracle Errors - *Optional\: Comma delimited list of Oracle errors to ignore while executing the import. Example\: ORA-31684,ORA-39111
 Instance Wrapper - *Required\: Jython call wrapper required to run as the Oracle Instance owner.
 Log File Name - No description
 Oracle Home - *Required\: Fully qualified pathname of the Oracle Home where the patch will be applied.
 Oracle SID - *Required\: The Oracle SID of the target database.
 Oracle Version - Version of the Oracle Home.
 Parameter File Name - *Required\: Full path to file containing parameter information for execution of the data pump import utility.
 Show Log File - *Required\: Will print the import log file contents to console and history pages if set to True. Default value is False.
 Temporary File Location - *Optional\: The location where all temporary output files will be placed. This directory will be removed at the completion of the workflow.
 XML Password - Optional\: If the XDB schema is present and cleanup is set to True then the XML database will be re-created and will require the XML database password to be provided.

 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Inputs\:
 command - executes GatherParametersforOracleDatabaseRefreshviaDataPump.py
 Data Pump Export Files - *Required\: One or more Data Pump Export Files. If more than one provide input as a comma delimited list.
 Data Pump Parameter File - *Optional\: Parameter File used with the Data Pump Import Utility. Default parameter values will be generated if Parameter File none provided.
 Inventory Files - *Optional\: Comma separated list of fully qualified Oracle inventory files. If not specified, default to /etc/oraInst.loc, /var/opt/oracle/oraInst.loc, or %ProgramFiles%\Oracle\Inventory.

 Oracle Home - *Optional\: The ORACLE_HOME to use if more than one home in the inventory file(s)
 Oracle SID - *Required\: The Oracle Server (Instance) ID
 Server Wrapper - *Required\: String to execute routine as server superuser.
 Target Directory - *Required\: Directory where Data Pump dump and Parameter files are to be staged on target database server. Must be known to the Oracle Instance.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Data Pump Export Files - One or more Data Pump Export Files. If more than one output is formatted as a comma delimited list.
 Data Pump Parameter File - Parameter File used with the Data Pump Import Utility. Default will be generated if none provided.
 Inventory Files - Comma separated list of fully qualified Oracle inventory files. If not specified, default to /etc/oraInst.loc, /var/opt/oracle/oraInst.loc, or %ProgramFiles%\Oracle\Inventory.

 Oracle Home - The ORACLE_HOME to use if more than one home in the inventory file(s)
 Oracle SID - The Oracle Server (Instance) ID
 Target Directory - Directory to place Data Pump export and parameter files. Must be known to the Oracle Instance.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 e64c3929-d8fa-49de-bd09-802c32a5f72b.d849def8-f647-4840-8424-51dff888fc02.description=Description\:
 During this step, the Data Pump import parameters to be used in the database refresh task are collected and validated. The collected parameters determine what actions Data Pump should take when tables are found to be in existence. Possible Data Pump actions in this context are\:
- Drop and recreate the tables
- Ignore the tables
- Append rows to the table
The parameters also indicate whether or not to import data into system tables.

 Job Name - *Optional\: Name of the import job to create.

 e64c3929-d8fa-49de-bd09-802c32a5f72b.description=<pre>
 Purpose

Restore a full database from an Oracle Data Pump export dump file onto a target Oracle database server.

 Description

The Database Refresh is conducted using the Data Pump export file(s) and an optional supplied parameter file. The files and target system is then subjected to a series of validation checks. If the file(s) together with the target database server passes through the prerequisite checks, the Data Pump export dump file will be restored onto the target database server. Appropriate messages will be provided throughout the workflow should there be any issues encountered. Encryption, compression, size of dump files are handled by defining proper entries in the parameter file.

 Usage Instructions

User supplies all the necessary required data in the deployment parameter page. The target directory in the parameter file represents the path associated with the Oracle directory object and must be pre-created prior to execution of this workflow. This is the location where the export Data Pump dump files are located and where the refresh task will read all necessary needed files. The workflow will use its default values whenever optional fields are not populated. If the user left the Data Pump Parameter File field blank the workflow will generate a parameter file to be used based on supplied data on the deployment page, and workflow generated values.


 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Data Pump Export Files - *Required\: One or more Data Pump Export Files. If more than one provide input as a comma delimited list.
 Instance.Name - No description
 Instance.os user - No description
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Server.Become User - No description
 Target Directory - *Required\: Directory where Data Pump dump and Parameter files are to be staged on target database server. Must be known to the Oracle Instance.

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Oracle DB User Password - *Optional\: Required only if the DB User Password should not be '/ as sysdba'.
 Data Options - *Optional\: The DATA_OPTIONS parameter provides options for how to handle certain types of data during exports and imports. The only valid option for this parameter is SKIP_CONSTRAINT_ERRORS.
 Schema - *Optional\: Specifies that a schema-mode import is to be performed
 Show Log File - *Optional\: Will print the import log file contents to console and history pages if set to True. Default value is False.
 Verification Result - No description
 Parallel - *Optional\: Change the number of active workers for current import job.
 Oracle DB User - *Optional\: Database User account if other than sysdba. Must have required privileges or workflow will fail.
 Table Exist Action - No description
 Tables - *Optional\: Specifies that you want to perform a table-mode import.
 Verification SQL Script - No description
 Partition Options - *Optional\: Specifies how table partitions should be created during an import operation.
 Oracle Account - *Optional\: Oracle user that owns the ORACLE_HOME on target database server. Required if inventory does not exist. Left blank for Windows.
 Exclude - *Optional\: Enables you to filter the metadata that is imported by specifying objects and object types that you want to exclude from the import job. Example\: TABLE\:"LIKE'TABLE_NAME%'",VIEW\:"LIKE'VIEW_NAME%'"
 Encryption Password - No description
 Remap Tablespace - *Optional\: Remaps all objects selected for import with persistent data in the source tablespace to be created in the target tablespace.
 Update System Tables - *Optional\: Set to 'True' to update system tables as part of refresh. Set to 'False' to NOT update system tables as part of refresh. Default is 'False'.
 Cleanup Users Exclude - Optional\: Comma separated list of database users that should be excluded from the cleanup process.
 Remap Datafile - *Optional\: Comma separated key value pair of Tablespace Name\:Location of tablespace datafiles. Example\: USERS\:/u01/app/oracle/oradata/orca,SCOTT\:/u01/app/oracle/oradata/orca.)
 Include - *Optional\: Enables you to filter the metadata that is imported by specifying objects and object types for the current import mode. Example\: TABLE\:"LIKE'TABLE_NAME%'",VIEW\:"LIKE'VIEW_NAME%'"
 Cleanup Database - Optional\: If value is set to True cleanup will occur on the database and attempt to drop all non-default schemas. Default value is False.
 Data Pump Parameter File - *Optional\: Parameter File used with the Data Pump Import Utility. Default parameter values will be generated if Parameter File none provided.
 Tablespaces - *Optional\: Specifies that you want to perform a tablespace-mode import.
 Remap Data - *Optional\: This parameter allows you to remap data as it is being inserted into a new database.
 XML Password - Optional\: If the XDB schema is present and cleanup is set to True then the XML database will be re-created and will require the XML database password to be provided.
 Job Name - *Optional\: Name of the import job to create.
 Ignorable Oracle Errors - *Optional\: Comma separated list of Oracle errors that can be ignored if the occur. (i.e. ORA-31684,ORA-39111,etc.)
 Content - No description

 Dependencies

SA Agents must be installed on all target servers. Target Directory supplied in the Deployment Page must be pre-created in the operating system. Supplied Oracle user must have access to the provided Target Directory. Oracle directory to be used by Data Pump must exist prior workflow execution. Oracle user must have read/write access to Oracle object directory associated path.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
